{"abstract": "Wealthy art collectors are benefiting from tax breaks when they build museums with limited public access, often near their homes.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/11/business/art-collectors-gain-tax-benefits-from-private-museums.html", "snippet": "Wealthy art collectors are benefiting from tax breaks when they build museums with limited public access, often near their homes.", "lead_paragraph": "The Brant Foundation Art Study Center \u2014 a picturesque gallery space inside a converted 1902 stone barn \u2014 is just down the road from the Greenwich, Conn., estate of its creator, Peter M. Brant, the newsprint magnate and avid art collector. There are no identifying signs for the center, whether at the turnoff on North Street, at the security gate or on the building itself, though the location is known to the art-world cognoscenti and celebrities who attend the twice-a-year gala openings, held at the private polo club next door that Mr. Brant also founded. Visits to the center itself are by appointment only.", "print_section": "BU", "print_page": "1", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/11/business/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "height": 466, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/01/11/business/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 466}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/11/business/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2-jumbo-v2.jpg", "height": 795, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2015/01/11/business/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2/11-MUSEUMTAX-JP2-superJumbo-v2.jpg", "height": 1590, "width": 2048,